<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-106-858  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 106 858.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Design  Jan 15 1990 v29 n2 p23(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>No challenge too small for pocket computer team: an inside look atPoqet Computer's time-to-market team.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Kass, Elliott.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Poqet Computer (Sunnyvale, CA) time-to-market productdevelopment team, led by Poqet co-founder and VP of AdvancedTechnology John Fairbanks, found that it was able to realize thefull range of features that it desired in the Poqet pocket-sizedcomputer because no other firm was attempting to develop a similarproduct.andP;  The Poqet was envisioned as an MSDOS-based computerpowered by conventional alkaline batteries, but the tiny computerrequired creativity, several technological innovations, close teamcooperation, a flexible project manager with effective personnelmanagement skills (Fairbanks), engineers with multiple technicalskills, adequate investment, and a skilled procurement manager.andO;Once Poqet gained funding from Fujitsu in early 1989, Peter Dixonwas hired as procurement manager to develop a viable network ofsuppliers.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Poqet Computer Corp. (product development).andO;Topic:     CompaniesCase StudyProduct DevelopmentLaptop ComputersManagement StyleVendor RelationsExecutive.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>